---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const topicGroups = [
  {
    title: "Why Privacy Matters",
    intro:
      "Explore the social, political, and economic consequences of living without privacy protections.",
    items: [
      {
        question: "How does surveillance capitalism impact me?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Advertising networks harvest every click, location ping, and purchase to build behavioral profiles that predict what we do next.",
          },
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Those profiles are sold to the highest bidder, concentrating power among a handful of platforms that can steer information, culture, and politics at scale.",
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        question: "Why is metadata exposure dangerous even with encryption?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Metadata reveals who you talk to, when, and how often. These patterns expose relationships, routines, and vulnerabilities—sometimes more than message contents would.",
          },
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Protecting privacy requires minimizing both content and metadata exposure so adversaries cannot map your social graph.",
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        question: "What does algorithmic manipulation mean for society?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Recommendation systems decide what we see online. Without accountability, they can nudge public opinion or behavior without our knowledge.",
          },
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Understanding these dynamics helps communities push for dignified, autonomy-respecting technology.",
          },
        ],
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    title: "Essential Concepts",
    intro:
      "Start with the core ideas that underpin private communication and resilient digital ecosystems.",
    items: [
      {
        question: "What is metadata?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Metadata is data about data: who sent a message, when it was sent, how large it was, and where it originated.",
          },
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Like the outside of an envelope, metadata offers clues that investigators combine to map social graphs or identify whistleblowers.",
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        question: "What is end-to-end encryption?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "End-to-end encryption ensures only the sender and recipient can read a message. Services like Signal and WhatsApp use it to prevent eavesdropping by intermediaries.",
          },
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "However, encryption alone does not hide metadata. True privacy pairs encryption with anonymization to obscure who is communicating.",
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        question: "What is decentralization?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Decentralization distributes control across many operators so that communities can run their own infrastructure, as seen in the Fediverse.",
          },
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "It is a powerful step, yet without metadata protection decentralized systems can still leak who is talking to whom.",
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        question: "What is anonymization?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Anonymization hides the link between people and their data flows using techniques like traffic mixing, blind relays, and capability-based access.",
          },
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Journal Foundation focuses on anonymization because decentralization alone leaves users exposed to surveillance capitalism and nation-state adversaries.",
          },
        ],
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    title: "Practical Guides",
    intro:
      "Apply privacy concepts to your daily life with approachable, task-focused walkthroughs.",
    items: [
      {
        question: "How do I evaluate a \"privacy-focused\" app?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Look beyond marketing. Investigate whether the app collects metadata, centralizes trust, or monetizes attention through ads.",
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        question: "How do I read a privacy policy?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Scan for data retention periods, third-party sharing, and whether the provider reserves the right to sell or reuse your information.",
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        question: "How do I enable Global Privacy Control?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Use browsers and extensions that broadcast the Global Privacy Control signal, and confirm the websites you rely on honor it.",
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        question: "How do I use Signal safely?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Enable disappearing messages, registration lock, and keep your device operating system patched to reduce risks from physical access.",
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        question: "How do I understand app permissions?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Review which sensors or data stores an app can access, and revoke permissions that are unrelated to its core function.",
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        question: "How do I protect myself from surveillance?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Combine encrypted messaging, anonymized browsing, and compartmentalized identities to limit how much anyone can learn about you.",
          },
        ],
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    title: "Advanced Topics",
    intro:
      "When you are ready, dive into deeper explorations of threat modeling and systemic risks.",
    items: [
      {
        question: "How do I create a threat model?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Start by asking who you are protecting against, what they can access, and the consequences if they succeed.",
          },
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Design layered safeguards so that one failure does not expose everything you care about.",
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        question: "What is the China Problem?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "States capable of bulk data seizure and future quantum decryption can store encrypted archives today and decode them later.",
          },
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Minimize what leaves your vault, and assume anything stored indefinitely could someday be read.",
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        question: "Why is \"I have nothing to hide\" wrong?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Privacy is about dignity, autonomy, and the freedom to experiment without constant observation—not about hiding wrongdoing.",
          },
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "When privacy erodes, marginalized communities lose the ability to organize, heal, and advocate safely.",
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        question: "How does influence work at scale?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Data brokers and recommendation engines weaponize attention to move markets and elections.",
          },
          {
            type: "text",
            content:
              "Learning how narratives are targeted helps inoculate communities against manipulation.",
          },
        ],
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    title: "Further Resources",
    intro: "Continue your learning with trusted organizations and Journal Foundation publications.",
    items: [
      {
        question: "Where can I find credible privacy resources?",
        answer: [
          {
            type: "text",
            content: "Explore these recommended readings and tools:",
          },
          {
            type: "html",
            content: `<ul>
              <li><a href="/whitepapers">Journal Foundation whitepapers</a></li>
              <li><a href="/stack">Learn about the protocol stack</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.eff.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Electronic Frontier Foundation</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.torproject.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tor Project</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.privacyguides.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Privacy Guides</a></li>
            </ul>`,
          },
        ],
      },
    ],
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Learning Center — Journal Foundation"
  description="Explore privacy literacy resources on metadata, encryption, decentralization, and anonymization for every skill level."
>
  <main class="learn-page">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>Privacy Learning Center</h1>
        <p class="lead">Understand digital privacy, security, and sovereignty—whether or not you ever use our protocols.</p>
        <p>
          Journal Foundation publishes education for everyone: students, organizers, policymakers, technologists,
          and people just beginning to question how their data is used. Start with the essentials, then dive into
          advanced topics when you are ready.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="topics">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Learn at Your Own Pace</h2>
        <p class="section-lead">
          Browse the questions below and expand the areas that match your current goals. Whether you are new to privacy or
          refining an advanced practice, each topic distills key takeaways into an accessible format.
        </p>

        <div class="accordion" role="list">
          {topicGroups.map((group) => (
            <article class="topic-group" role="listitem">
              <header class="group-header">
                <h3>{group.title}</h3>
                <p>{group.intro}</p>
              </header>
              <ul class="collapsible-list">
                {group.items.map((item) => (
                  <li>
                    <details>
                      <summary>{item.question}</summary>
                      <div class="answer">
                        {item.answer.map((block) =>
                          block.type === "html" ? (
                            <div class="rich-block" set:html={block.content} />
                          ) : (
                            <p>{block.content}</p>
                          )
                        )}
                      </div>
                    </details>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <style>
    .learn-page {
      padding-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
    }

    .hero {
      padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
    }

    .lead {
      font-size: var(--step-1);
      color: var(--color-text-primary);
      margin-top: var(--space-md);
    }

    section {
      padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    }

    .topics {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(28, 42, 68, 0.35) 0%, rgba(10, 14, 20, 0.75) 100%);
    }

    .section-lead {
      max-width: 60ch;
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    }

    .accordion {
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-2xl);
    }

    .topic-group {
      background: rgba(17, 27, 42, 0.65);
      border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
      padding: var(--space-xl);
      box-shadow: 0 30px 60px rgba(5, 10, 25, 0.25);
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-xl);
    }

    .group-header h3 {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
      font-size: var(--step-2);
    }

    .group-header p {
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
      max-width: 60ch;
    }

    .collapsible-list {
      list-style: none;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-sm);
    }

    details {
      background: rgba(20, 32, 52, 0.9);
      border: 1px solid rgba(65, 125, 255, 0.25);
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      padding: var(--space-md) var(--space-lg);
      transition: border-color 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
    }

    details[open] {
      border-color: rgba(90, 150, 255, 0.65);
      box-shadow: 0 12px 30px rgba(32, 70, 150, 0.25);
    }

    summary {
      cursor: pointer;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: var(--step-0);
      list-style: none;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: var(--space-sm);
    }

    summary::-webkit-details-marker {
      display: none;
    }

    summary::after {
      content: "+";
      font-size: var(--step-2);
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
      transition: transform 0.2s ease;
    }

    details[open] summary::after {
      transform: rotate(45deg);
    }

    .answer {
      margin-top: var(--space-md);
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-sm);
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    }

    .answer p {
      margin: 0;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .answer ul {
      margin: 0;
      padding-left: var(--space-xl);
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .rich-block :global(a) {
      color: var(--color-accent-primary);
    }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .topic-group {
        padding: var(--space-lg);
      }

      summary {
        font-size: var(--step--1);
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
